==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingle
<hw>In"gle</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧"g'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael. &
Ir. <ets>aingeali</ets> fire; cf. L. <ets>igniculusi</ets> spark, dim.
of <ets>ignis</ets> fire. Cf. <er>Ignite</er>.]</ety> <def>Flame; blaze;
a fire; a fireplace.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ingle nook</b></col>, <cd>the chimney corner.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Ingle side</b></col>, <col><b>Ingle
cheek</b></col></mcol>, <cd>the fireside.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ingle
<hw>In"gle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also <ets>engle</ets>,
<ets>enghle</ets>: cf. Gael. & Ir. <ets>aingeal</ets> an angel. Cf.
<er>Engle</er>.]</ety> <def>A paramour; a favourite; a sweetheart; an
engle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Toone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 763 --></p>

<p><ent>Ingle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ingle
<hw>In"gle</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧"g'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
cajole or coax; to wheedle. See <er>Engle</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

